node.text:
It was a weekend full of celebration, families, and honoring the hard work of our students as they transition to #OUalumni. We’re still not over it. 

No matter where life takes you next, remember you’ll always have a home at the University of Oklahoma. Congratulations, 2020 & 2021 graduates! We are proud of you. ❤️🎓☝🏼

node.text:
As we prepare to celebrate and honor our graduates in the Classes of 2020 and 2021 this weekend, we take time to reflect on a year unlike any other.

This journey has given us a new perspective, but our goal remains the same - to live out what it means to be part of the #OUFamily and to do so together. Live On, 2021. ☝🏼

Thank you to our OU family. This semester was possible because of you. Live On, University! ☝🏼

node.text:
🗣 Hey #OU2025! 

We’re officially ☝🏼 ONE MONTH ☝🏼away from 2021 Move-In! We can’t wait to have you here on campus to kickoff a great semester ahead, but before you call OU home, be sure you have everything you need including information about this year’s Move-In. 

Be sure to stay up-to-date with all the information you need by following @ou_housingandfood, as well as visiting ou.edu/housingandfood/move-in. We look forward to welcoming you home! ⭕️🙌🏼

node.text:
Yesterday, we had the honor of welcoming students from the Boys & Girls Club of Norman to spend the afternoon with @oubigevent, @ouleader, and @ou_football! 

From running drills with the football team to spending time growing in friendships and experiencing a team-like atmosphere, we extend our thanks to students and volunteers for spending yesterday with us on campus! You’ll always be part of the #OUFamily.

To learn more, please visit link.ou.edu/2SEZ8q2.

node.text: The University of Oklahoma recognizes and celebrates Juneteenth as a part of our nation’s history. Today, we celebrate freedom while recognizing Black culture and history. Happy Juneteenth to our #OUFamily.
